      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@SergioDemianLerner I'm in favor of removing OP_CODESEPARATOR, but I think you mean a soft fork. As far as I know, there has never ever been a hard fork in Bitcoin's history (but we'll do one in 1 month...). Also, there's no need for one here. Simpy turn OP_CODESEPARATOR into a 'return false' - no need to add new semantics.\n\nWhat do you mean by putting a \"*\" in the script?\n",
