   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "If we're going to do an actual hard fork for the script language, give me a few days and I can come up with tons of small fixes. If we're not scared of redoing the scripting language from scratch (I am, however), I think we can come up with something vastly better (except for being tested).\n\nHowever, removing the atrocity that is OP_CODESEPARATOR is as easy as replacing it with \"return false;\", and can be done with a simple soft fork like we've done several times already now.\n",
