      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "If ever the signature verification procedure is changed, I would simplify it more: \nLet T0 be the original transaction.\nT1 = T0 with all scriptsigs cleared.\nLet X = SHA-256 ( SHA-256 ( T1 )  )\nThen HashTransaction(T) = SHA-256 ( X  ||  n ))  )\nWhere n is the input number to be verified. Then  X could be cached and computed only once for the whole transaction (here I'm not taking into account the SIG_ flags)\n\nBut this is only a dream. I doubt the the signature verification system would ever be changed.\n",
